BUILDING AND RUNNING A QT EMULATOR

===========
BUILDING QT
===========

For Linux and Windows, you will need to build Qt from source using the same toolchains you use to build emulator. You will need to have a different
build of Qt for each host platform (32+64-bit Windows and Linux).

On Mac, you may be able to use the binary distribution of the libraries; give it a shot.

To build it, download the source, and from the <Qt home>/src directory, configure and build. Here's an example to build the 32-bit Linux libraries.

export CC=<path to source tree>/prebuilts/gcc/linux-x86/host/x86_64-linux-glibc2.11-4.8/bin/x86_64-linux-gcc
export CXX=<path to source tree>/prebuilts/gcc/linux-x86/host/x86_64-linux-glibc2.11-4.8/bin/x86_64-linux-gcc
./configure -prefix <Qt home>/5.4/gcc_32 -platform linux-g++-32 -opensource -confirm-license -no-openssl -no-compile-examples
make -j80 clean
make -j80 install

To confiure Qt for cross compilation to Windows from a Linux GCC host (64-bit):

./configure -prefix <Qt home>/5.4/x86_64-w64-mingw32 -developer-build -opensource -confirm-license -dbus -xplatform win32-g++ -device-option CROSS_COMPILE=x86_64-w64-mingw32- -nomake examples -nomake tests -no-warnings-are-errors -silent

=================
BUILDING EMULATOR
=================

In the android/skin/qt directory,

    find . | grep Makefile | xargs rm
    /path/to/Qt/5.4/<qt-architecture>/bin/qmake
    make
    
    Note that you'll generally need to build twice; once for 32-bit and once for 64-bit. The libraries go into
    external/qemu/objs, and the two different versions won't clobber each other.

In Makefile.common,

    EMULATOR_USE_QT ?= true
    EMULATOR_USE_SDL2 ?= false

    adjust QT_HOME

In android/config/config.h:

    //#define CONFIG_SDL 1
    #define CONFIG_QT 1

=======
RUNNING
=======

Windows:

    QT_PLUGIN_PATH=<Qt home>/5.4/x86_64-w64-mingw32/plugins

MacOS:

    DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH=<Qt home>/5.4/clang_64/plugins/platforms:<path to source tree>/external/qemu/objs/lib64

Linux:

    LD_LIBRARY_PATH=<path to source tree>/external/qemu/objs/lib64